  <section id="healthcare-system">
    <h2>Healthcare System Overview</h2>
    <p>
      Malta's healthcare punches above its weight for a small island nation. The public system provides good care, and proximity to Italy and northern Europe enables easy access to specialists when needed.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Mater Dei Hospital</strong> is Malta's main public facility—modern, well-equipped, and handling most medical needs. Opened in 2007, it replaced older facilities and provides comprehensive services including cardiac surgery, oncology, and most specialties. Emergency care is efficient.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Private hospitals</strong> including St. James Hospital and various clinics offer alternatives with shorter waits and private rooms. Quality is good for routine procedures. Complex cases may still transfer to public or seek overseas care.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Specialist limitations:</strong> Some subspecialties have limited local availability—Malta's 500,000 population can't support every specialization. For rare conditions or complex procedures, evacuation to Italy, UK, or Germany provides access to world-class centers just 1-3 hours away.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>English availability:</strong> Excellent throughout healthcare. All doctors speak English, hospital documentation is bilingual, and patient communication works entirely in English. This is Malta's key healthcare advantage.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Prescription medications:</strong> Well-stocked pharmacies with European medication availability. EHIC/public healthcare covers prescriptions for eligible residents. Prices are reasonable by European standards. Rarely issues finding standard medications.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="costs">
    <h2>Cost Planning</h2>
    <p>
      Malta is more expensive than Eastern Mediterranean alternatives but cheaper than Western Europe. The compact size reduces transport costs, and the public healthcare system limits medical expenses for residents.
    </p>
    <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />
    <p>
      <strong>Total monthly budget</strong> for comfortable retirement with comprehensive health coverage typically ranges from €2,800-4,500 depending on location and lifestyle. Sliema/St Julians area runs €3,200-4,500; Valletta vicinity €2,800-4,000; Gozo offers value at €2,200-3,200.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Housing dominates costs.</strong> Malta's small size and growing popularity have pushed property prices and rents upward. Budget significantly for housing—it's the largest expense. Purchasing may offer better value than renting for long-term residents.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Healthcare cost strategy:</strong> International insurance runs €400-800/month for seniors. Using Malta's free public healthcare for routine needs while maintaining international coverage for complex care and evacuation balances protection with cost efficiency.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>No car necessary:</strong> Malta's public transport, walkability, and small size mean many retirees live without cars—significant monthly savings compared to car-dependent destinations. Taxis and ride-sharing fill gaps affordably.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="faqs">
    <h2>Common Questions</h2>

    <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 mt-6">
      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border border-neutral-200 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Is Malta crowded?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">Yes—Malta is one of the world's most densely populated countries. Main island areas are busy, traffic can be heavy, and summer tourism adds to crowds. Gozo is quieter. If you need space and solitude, Malta may feel cramped.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border border-neutral-200 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">How hot are summers?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">Hot—July/August regularly hits 35°C (95°F) with high humidity. Sea breezes help coastal areas, but air conditioning is essential for comfort. Many retirees travel during peak summer or stay indoors midday.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border border-neutral-200 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Can I rely on public healthcare entirely?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">For routine care, yes—quality is good and it's free. However, waiting lists exist for non-urgent procedures, and some specialties have limited capacity. Insurance is required for residence anyway and provides peace of mind for complex situations.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border border-neutral-200 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">What's the British expat community like?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">Substantial—estimated 10,000+ British residents. Clubs, social groups, British pubs, and established networks exist. Easy to find compatriots if desired. The community is aging but active, with support systems for newcomers.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border border-neutral-200 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Should I consider Gozo instead of Malta?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">Gozo offers lower costs, less crowding, and more rural character. Healthcare is more limited—serious cases transfer to Malta's main island. Good choice if you prioritize tranquility over convenience. Ferry connections to Malta are frequent.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border border-neutral-200 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">How does Malta Retirement Programme tax treatment work?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">Qualifying pension income remitted to Malta is taxed at 15% flat rate (minimum €7,500 tax annually). Income kept outside Malta is not taxed. Complex rules apply—professional tax advice is essential before committing to MRP.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready to Plan Your Malta Retirement?"
    description="Get personalized quotes from insurers experienced with Malta retirement. Coverage meeting residence requirements with European network access."
    buttonText="Get Your Quotes"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna"
  />
</PageShell>
